KW  - Asymmetric preferences
KW  - Prudence
KW  - Game-theoretical models of monetary policy
KW  - ARCH
AB  - This paper tests the predictions of the Barro–Gordon model using US data on inflation and unemployment. To that end, it constructs a general game-theoretical model with asymmetric preferences that nests the Barro–Gordon model and a version of Cukierman's model as special cases. Likelihood Ratio tests indicate that the restriction imposed by the Barro–Gordon model is rejected by the data but the one imposed by the version of Cukierman's model is not. Reduced-form estimates are consistent with the view that the Federal Reserve weights more heavily positive than negative unemployment deviations from the expected natural rate.
